29/03/2007
ROME, Italy -- Macedonian Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki met with government and parliamentary officials in Rome on Wednesday (March 28th) and said they assured him that Italy backs Macedonia's aspirations for EU accession. Milososki noted, however, that he was again told that Macedonia must fulfil set reforms to meet the criteria for membership.
In other news, US Deputy Assistant Defence Secretary Daniel P. Fata visited Skopje on Wednesday for talks with President Branko Crvenkovski and Defence Ministry officials. Fata reiterated the need to boost key reforms in Macedonia, to improve chances for an invitation to NATO membership next year. (A1 TV, MIA - 28/03/07) 
